  stimulus_text = 'Although the invention of the steam engine revolutionized industry and transportation, it also brought with it significant consequences for workers, especially those in the coal industry. The introduction of steam-powered machinery meant that many jobs formerly done by hand could now be done by machines, leading to widespread unemployment and a decrease in wages. Workers had to adapt to new skills and new ways of working, or else face being left behind in the increasingly industrialized world.  In the long run, however, the invention of the steam engine ushered in an era of increased economic productivity and technological advancement, ultimately leading to a higher standard of living for many.',
